👉 this keyword

this refers to the current object of the class.

Main Uses of this

1. To refer current object variables
Used when local variables and instance variables have same name.

class Student {
    int id;

    Student(int id) {
        this.id = id; // this.id = instance variable
    }
}

2. To call current class constructor

class Demo {
    Demo() {
        this(10); // calls parameterized constructor
        System.out.println("Default constructor");
    }

    Demo(int x) {
        System.out.println("Parameterized constructor");
    }
}

3. To pass current object as argument

void display(Demo obj) {
    System.out.println("Method called");
}

void show() {
    display(this);
}

4. To return current object

Demo getObject() {
    return this;
}
